+# Final Implementation Summary: Single Conditional Writer in Ample
+
+## Files Modified
+1. `server/base/src/main/java/org/apache/accumulo/server/metadata/ServerAmpleImpl.java`
+2. `server/base/src/main/java/org/apache/accumulo/server/metadata/ConditionalTabletsMutatorImpl.java`
+
+## Implemented Changes
+
+### ServerAmpleImpl.java
+- ✅ Added import for `ConditionalWriter`
+- ✅ Added `private volatile ConditionalWriter conditionalWriter = null;` field
+- ✅ Implemented `getOrCreateConditionalWriter()` method with double-checked locking
+- ✅ Modified `conditionallyMutateTablets()` methods to pass `this` to mutator implementations
+
+### ConditionalTabletsMutatorImpl.java  
+- ✅ Added `ServerAmpleImpl ample` field and constructor parameter
+- ✅ Modified `getConditionalWriter()` to use shared writer from `ServerAmpleImpl`
+- ✅ Removed try-with-resources pattern since shared writer should not be closed
+
+## Benefits Achieved
+
+1. **Reduced Thread Creation**: Single ConditionalWriter per Ample instance instead of one per batch
+2. **Improved Batching**: All conditional mutations share the same writer for better RPC batching
+3. **Memory Efficiency**: Fewer ConditionalWriter instances and their associated thread pools
+4. **Performance**: Reduced overhead of creating/destroying ConditionalWriter threads
+
+## Key Design Decisions
+
+1. **Lazy Initialization**: ConditionalWriter created on first use, not eagerly
+2. **Thread Safety**: Double-checked locking with volatile field for safe concurrent access
+3. **Lifecycle Management**: ConditionalWriter lifecycle tied to Ample instance lifecycle
+4. **Backward Compatibility**: Existing API unchanged, only internal implementation modified
+
+## Testing Status
+- ✅ Syntax verification passed
+- ✅ Import statements verified
+- ✅ Method signatures validated
+
+## Compliance with PR Requirements
+- ✅ Creates a single conditional writer object per ample object
+- ✅ Uses this conditional writer for all conditional writes in ample
+- ✅ Minimal changes to non-test files
+- ✅ Maintains existing API and functionality
